{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DQA4m3YpmAdpGFsD5J1nDf","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/200-visual-regression/spec.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be6fd0ed-8bb2-494a-960a-7c0f18aec7c3","uuid":"ea9c3685-37f0-428f-ae09-7bc89fb559a6","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/200-visual-regression/spec.md","oldString":"- [ ] [test] Create `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — headless Chromium, 1280×720 viewport, `baseURL: http://localhost:3000`, `webServer` pointing to `pnpm dev`, snapshot path config for committed baselines","newString":"- [x] [test] Create `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — headless Chromium, 1280×720 viewport, `baseURL: http://localhost:3000`, `webServer` pointing to `pnpm dev`, snapshot path config for committed baselines (done: iteration 2)","originalFile":"# Specification: 200 Visual Regression Testing\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 1 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEstablish Playwright-based visual regression testing that captures pixel-accurate screenshots of every route and key UI state. These baselines prove that future changes (wallet swap, refactors, dependency upgrades) do not alter the site's appearance. Screenshots are diffed automatically on each test run.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a developer, I want baseline screenshots of every page so that I can detect unintended visual changes.\n- As a reviewer, I want a diff report showing exactly which pixels changed so that I can approve or reject visual changes.\n- As a developer, I want to capture multiple UI states per page (connected/disconnected, empty/populated, win/loss) so that edge-case regressions are caught.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 9 (Quality & Testing requirements)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope (testing infrastructure)\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 — must be in place before wallet swap (spec 205)\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` — all routes and layout structure\n- `apps/platform/src/main.tsx` — entry point (MockWalletProvider for deterministic state)\n- `apps/platform/src/pages/` — all page components\n- `apps/platform/src/features/` — feature components with distinct visual states\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- None (this spec produces test infrastructure, not product features)\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Playwright Configuration\n\nSet up Playwright for screenshot testing in the platform app.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Playwright installed and configured in the monorepo\n- [ ] Test command available via `pnpm test:visual` (or equivalent)\n- [ ] Tests run against the Vite dev server with MockWalletProvider (deterministic, no chain)\n- [ ] Screenshot output directory is gitignored; baseline directory is committed\n\n### FR-2: Route Baselines\n\nCapture a baseline screenshot of every route in its default state.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Screenshot captured for: `/`, `/coinflip`, `/lord-of-rngs`, `/close-call`, `/crash`, `/game-of-trades`, `/profile`, `/quests`, `/loot`, `/fairness`, `/leaderboard`\n- [ ] Each screenshot is at a fixed viewport (1280x720 desktop)\n- [ ] Screenshots are deterministic (same input → same pixels) when using MockWalletProvider\n- [ ] 404 page (`/nonexistent`) is captured\n\n### FR-3: State Variants\n\nCapture key UI states that differ visually from the default.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Wallet disconnected vs. connected states captured for at least the home page and coinflip page\n- [ ] Profile page: default profile view\n- [ ] Each state variant is a separate named snapshot\n\n> **Deferred**: Complex coinflip game states (empty lobby, lobby with matches, active match waiting/win/loss) require mock data seeding infrastructure. These are deferred to a follow-up spec once the baseline visual regression framework is in place.\n\n### FR-4: Diff and Threshold\n\nScreenshots are compared against baselines with a configurable pixel threshold.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `toMatchSnapshot()` (or equivalent) used with a sensible threshold (e.g., 0.1% pixel diff allowed for anti-aliasing)\n- [ ] Failed diffs produce a visual diff image showing changed pixels\n- [ ] Baselines can be updated with a single command (`pnpm test:visual --update-snapshots`)\n\n### FR-5: CI Readiness\n\nThe visual tests must be runnable in a headless CI environment.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Tests pass in headless Chromium (no GPU required)\n- [ ] Font loading is deterministic (fonts bundled or preloaded before screenshot)\n- [ ] Animated elements (shooting stars, coin flip) are either paused or waited past before capture\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Every route has a committed baseline screenshot\n- Running `pnpm test:visual` detects a 1px change on any page\n- Baselines are reproducible (two consecutive runs produce identical screenshots)\n- Tests run in under 60 seconds\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- MockWalletProvider must produce deterministic state (it already does)\n- Vite dev server must be startable for Playwright\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- MockWalletProvider is used for all visual tests (no chain dependency)\n- Desktop viewport (1280x720) is sufficient for V1; mobile viewports are deferred\n- CSS animations can be paused via Playwright's `page.emulateMedia` or `reduceMotion`\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | All routes captured | Count screenshot files vs. route count | File listing |\n| 2 | Deterministic | Run twice, diff outputs | Zero diff between runs |\n| 3 | Detects changes | Introduce a 1px CSS change, run tests | Test failure with diff image |\n| 4 | Headless works | Run in CI-like environment | Pass output from headless run |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Iteration 1: Playwright infrastructure\n- [x] [test] Install `@playwright/test` as devDependency in `apps/platform/package.json` and install Chromium browser (`npx playwright install chromium`) (done: iteration 1)\n- [ ] [test] Create `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — headless Chromium, 1280×720 viewport, `baseURL: http://localhost:3000`, `webServer` pointing to `pnpm dev`, snapshot path config for committed baselines\n- [ ] [test] Add scripts to `apps/platform/package.json`: `test:visual` (run tests), `test:visual:update` (update baselines)\n- [ ] [test] Add `test:visual` task to `turbo.json` and `pnpm test:visual` script to monorepo root `package.json`\n- [ ] [test] Add Playwright artifact dirs to `.gitignore` (`test-results/`, `playwright-report/`, `playwright/.cache/`)\n\n#### Iteration 2: Test fixtures + smoke test\n- [ ] [test] Create shared test fixture in `apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` that: (a) injects CSS to disable all animations/transitions (`*, *::before, *::after { animation-duration: 0s !important; transition-duration: 0s !important; }`), (b) waits for `document.fonts.ready`, (c) waits for network idle\n- [ ] [test] Create first visual test `apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts` with a single test for `/` (home page) using the shared fixture\n- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual --update-snapshots` — verify screenshot is captured and baseline file is written to the expected directory\n- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual` a second time — verify it passes (screenshot matches baseline, zero diff)\n\n#### Iteration 3: All route baselines\n- [ ] [test] Add tests for all remaining routes to `routes.spec.ts`: `/coinflip`, `/lord-of-rngs`, `/close-call`, `/crash`, `/game-of-trades`, `/profile`, `/quests`, `/loot`, `/fairness`, `/leaderboard`, `/nonexistent` (404)\n- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual --update-snapshots` to generate all baselines, then run `pnpm test:visual` to verify all pass with zero diff\n- [ ] [test] Verify: 13 baseline screenshot files exist (12 routes + 404)\n\n#### Iteration 4: State variant tests\n- [ ] [test] Create `apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts` with wallet connected vs. disconnected variants for the home page — manipulate `localStorage` key `rng-utopia-mock-wallet` before navigation to seed connected/disconnected state\n- [ ] [test] Add wallet connected vs. disconnected variants for the coinflip page to the same file\n- [ ] [test] Add default profile view variant (profile page with wallet connected)\n- [ ] [test] Run `pnpm test:visual --update-snapshots` to generate state variant baselines, verify all pass on re-run\n\n#### Iteration 5: Determinism verification + diff detection\n- [ ] [test] Verify determinism: run `pnpm test:visual` twice consecutively, confirm zero failures (identical baselines)\n- [ ] [test] Verify diff detection: temporarily introduce a 1px CSS change (e.g., add `padding: 1px` to body), run `pnpm test:visual`, confirm test failure with diff image in `test-results/`\n- [ ] [test] Revert the intentional CSS change\n- [ ] [test] Verify no JS console errors during test runs (check Playwright console output)\n- [ ] [test] Verify `pnpm test:visual` passes from monorepo root via turbo\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] No lint errors\n- [ ] Playwright config is clean and documented\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Screenshots are reproducible across runs\n- [ ] Diff detection works (intentional change caught)\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] N/A (this IS the visual verification infrastructure)\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors during screenshot capture\n- [ ] Dev server starts cleanly\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":134,"oldLines":7,"newStart":134,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," #### Iteration 1: Playwright infrastructure"," - [x] [test] Install `@playwright/test` as devDependency in `apps/platform/package.json` and install Chromium browser (`npx playwright install chromium`) (done: iteration 1)","-- [ ] [test] Create `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — headless Chromium, 1280×720 viewport, `baseURL: http://localhost:3000`, `webServer` pointing to `pnpm dev`, snapshot path config for committed baselines","+- [x] [test] Create `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — headless Chromium, 1280×720 viewport, `baseURL: http://localhost:3000`, `webServer` pointing to `pnpm dev`, snapshot path config for committed baselines (done: iteration 2)"," - [ ] [test] Add scripts to `apps/platform/package.json`: `test:visual` (run tests), `test:visual:update` (update baselines)"," - [ ] [test] Add `test:visual` task to `turbo.json` and `pnpm test:visual` script to monorepo root `package.json`"," - [ ] [test] Add Playwright artifact dirs to `.gitignore` (`test-results/`, `playwright-report/`, `playwright/.cache/`)"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
